raw_data.title: Certified Library Professional
raw_data.description: A Certified Library Professional is an individual who has obtained a formal certification in library science or a related field, demonstrating a recognized level of expertise and competency in library services. This certification is typically granted by a professional organization or governing body after the individual meets specific educational requirements, gains practical experience, and passes a certification exam. Certified Library Professionals are qualified to manage library operations, including cataloging, reference services, information literacy instruction, and collection development. They may work in various types of libraries, such as public, academic, or special libraries, and are often involved in community outreach, technology integration, and ensuring that library services meet the needs of diverse populations. Certification can enhance career prospects and is often seen as a mark of professionalism and commitment to the field of library science.

raw_data.title: IP Team Lead
raw_data.description: An IP (Intellectual Property) Team Lead is a managerial position responsible for overseeing a team that handles intellectual property matters within an organization. This role typically involves leading and coordinating efforts related to the protection, management, and enforcement of intellectual property assets, such as patents, trademarks, copyrights, and trade secrets. The IP Team Lead ensures that the team operates efficiently and in compliance with relevant laws and regulations, often collaborating with legal, R&D, and business development departments. Key responsibilities may include supervising the preparation and filing of IP applications, managing IP portfolios, conducting IP audits, providing strategic guidance on IP issues, and mentoring team members. The role requires strong leadership skills, deep knowledge of intellectual property law, and the ability to communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders. An IP Team Lead plays a critical role in safeguarding an organization's innovations and competitive advantage.
